name: v2.0.1
body:
## Changelog
* 210e971 Merge branch 'v2' of ssh://github.com/kayac/go-katsubushi into v2

name: v2.0.0
body:
## Changelog

- Added HTTP server.
- Added gRPC server.
- Change client library intafaces.
  - Pass `context.Context` to function arguments.

name: v1.7.0
body: - Support Redis Cluster #49

name: v1.6.2
body:
- Docker images on [ghcr.io](https://github.com/kayac/go-katsubushi/pkgs/container/go-katsubushi)
  - ARM64 images also available.
- Windows support #48 (@mattn)
- Fix race condition on tests #47 (@itchyny)

name: v1.6.1
body: Build by Go 1.17

name: v1.6.0
body:
Implement STAT via binary protocol #40 (@Songmu)

Build with Go 1.14.

name: v1.5.4
body:
Build with Go 1.12.
- migrate to go module #39

name: v1.5.3
body: Shutdown silently. Suppress WARN messages after a server shutdown. (#37)

name: v1.5.2
body:
- Suppress error output by warning at deadline exceeded. (#36)
- Add katsubushi.Clinet.SetTimeout() (#35)

name: v1.5.1
body: - Suppress error logs on EOF just after connected. (#34)

name: v1.5.0
body:
- Support binary protocol #29 @xorphitus 
  - Currentry, supported to get a single ID only.
- Refactor Dockerfile #32 @tkuchiki 
  - `worker_id` or `redis` option is must be required at boot a container.

name: v1.4.3
body:
- Fix goroutine (memory) leaks. #28
  - After v1.2.0.
- Fix a problem with release a lock on Redis for automated worker-id assignment. https://github.com/fujiwara/raus/pull/1

name: v1.4.2
body:
Includes bug fixes and performance improvement only from v1.4.1.

- Reduce memory allocation for Client (#22)
- travis: update go versions (#24)
- Fix race condition of STATS command (#25)

name: v1.4.1
body:
- No feature changes.
- use Monotonic time (#21)
  - katsubushi will serve a new ID even if OS time is rollbacked. (Go 1.9~)

name: v1.4.0
body:
- No feature changes.
- Refactored internal implementations and Client library.

name: v1.3.0
body:
- Add a client `katsubushi.Client`. #11 
- Fix race conditions. #12 
- Add `-min-worker-id` and `-max-worker-id` flag. #14 
- Load optional values from command line arguments and environment variables. #17 
- Switch a logger from logrus to zap #16

name: v1.2.0
body: Automated worker ID assignment by Redis.

name: v1.1.2
body: - Fix a crashing problem #8

name: v1.1.1
body:
- No code changes from v1.1.0
- fix `-version` output

name: v1.1.0
body: - Supports get_multi [#6](https://github.com/kayac/go-katsubushi/pull/6) ([fujiwara](https://github.com/fujiwara))

name: v1.0.0

- Supports unix domain socket
